main event: Possible satellite observation detected by ground-based radar on a 090-degree course
interesting points: The object was tracked for a duration of 30 minutes and covered a distance of 35 feet.
The report concludes that the object was likely a satellite, but notes that 6010 data (additional sensor data) was not available.
The report was part of Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force investigation into unidentified flying objects.
The report was forwarded to various military and intelligence agencies, including the National Indications Center (NIH-7) and the Defense Intelligence Agency (DIA).
